ODM leader Raila Odinga will tour Nakuru on Sunday, beginning his day with a church service at the K.A.G church in Mwisho wa Lami. Thereafter, the 2022 presidential hopeful will make a stopover in Mwisho wa Lami, Mau Narok, Likia and Mauche. He will also have several stop-overs at Stoo Mbili, Kihingo, Kwa Right and Njoro Posta before holding rallies at 140, Soko Mjinga and Mazembe Grounds. Meanwhile, UDA 2022 presidential candidate DP Ruto will be in Kajiado county on Sunday, beginning his day by attending a church service at AIC Llmasin Church in Kajiado.   